      "message": "Suppose you have 3 traces being watched by an alert:\ntrace_a: ---...\ntrace_b: - - . \ntrace_c: --   .\n\nAt the 4th commit, a regression is added (as seen in trace_a)\n\ntrace_b and trace_c get new data (filling in the missing points). Will they just be clustered against each other or will trace_a be included (since it also had the downshift)?",
