      "writtenOn": "2019-09-04T14:50:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For Android, the Group By is by device and branch because the data is sparse, and arrives based on those values, and Alerting is just done for each subset represented by the Group By options.\n\nFor example, if we group by config and arch then \"config\u003d8888,arch\u003dx86\" is a single\nsuch choice and all traces that match that will have clustering run over them.",
